      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"writing the code\" is just another way of saying \"trying harder,\" and i'm exhausted from trying. if we're talking about the actual genetics and neurology, isn't there a point where the biological blueprint just makes certain neurological states impossible? like, if my genes are hardwired for a certain level of baseline misery, isn't it just scientific fact that i'll never reach what others call \"normal\" happiness?",
